prompt:
Add a public function called FetchUrl to Effects.calr that represents a network request. It takes str parameter url and returns str. The function must declare the network effect.

Use this exact Calor network effect syntax:
§F{f001:FetchUrl:pub}
  §I{str:url}
  §O{str}
  §E{net:rw}
  §B{client} §C{HttpClient.new}§/C
  §B{response} §C{client.GetStringAsync}
    §A url
  §/C
  §R response
§/F{f001}

The §E{net:rw} declares the network effect:
- net:rw = network read/write access
- net:r = read only (GET requests)
- net:w = write only (POST/PUT requests)
- Required for any HTTP client operations
